Ivy needs:

Python 2.7
IPython 3.2.1 including notebook ("ipython notebook" should work)
ply -Python Lex Yacc) ("import ply" should work)
Z3 python interface ("import z3" should work)

symbolic link (linux) or directory junction (windows) from ~/.ipython/nbextensions/ivy to ivy/ivy

On windows, the best way to get IPython and ply is to install Anaconda: http://continuum.io/downloads

How to install on Ubuntu (tested on 14.04.3 64bit), all commands executed in ~:

sudo apt-get install git
sudo apt-get install python-pip
sudo apt-get install python-zmq
sudo pip install markupsafe
sudo pip install "ipython[all]==3.2.1"
sudo pip install ply
sudo apt-get install graphviz
dot -V # should work
wget https://github.com/Z3Prover/z3/releases/download/z3-4.4.1/z3-4.4.1-x64-ubuntu-14.04.zip
unzip z3-4.4.1-x64-ubuntu-14.04.zip
# add lines to .bashrc to add z3 bin directory to PYTHONPATH (and possibly PATH)
git clone -b automation https://github.com/odedp/ivy.git
ln -s ~/ivy/ivy ~/.ipython/nbextensions/ivy
# update firefox to version 44
wget http://www.cs.tau.ac.il/~odedp/ivy_lib.tar.gz
tar -xvf ivy_lib.tar.gz
ln -s ~/ivy_lib ~/ivy/ivy/lib
# change 'waitSeconds: 7' to 'waitSeconds: 0' in /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/IPython/html/static/components/requirejs/require.js


How to install on OSX (tested on OSX 10.9.5 x86_64, Darwin zaphod.local 13.4.0 Darwin Kernel Version 13.4.0: Sun Aug 17 19:50:11 PDT 2014; root:xnu-2422.115.4~1/RELEASE_X86_64 x86_64):

git clone -b automation https://github.com/odedp/ivy.git
# get python 2.7 and pip (pip is shipped with python 2.7.11)
pip install "ipython[all]==3.2.1"
pip install ply
# download and install Grahpviz from http://www.graphviz.org/Download_macos.php
wget https://github.com/Z3Prover/z3/releases/download/z3-4.4.1/z3-4.4.1-x64-osx-10.11.zip
unzip z3-4.4.1-x64-ubuntu-14.04.zip
# add lines to .bash_profile to add z3 bin directory to PYTHONPATH (and possibly PATH)
ln -s ~/ivy/ivy ~/.ipython/nbextensions/ivy
wget http://www.cs.tau.ac.il/~odedp/ivy_lib.tar.gz
tar -xvf ivy_lib.tar.gz
ln -s ~/ivy_lib ~/ivy/ivy/lib
# change 'waitSeconds: 7' to 'waitSeconds: 0' in requires.js:
sudo vi /Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/lib/python2.7/site-packages/IPython/html/static/components/requirejs/require.js
